            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          }
        },
        "lottkarr": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Lottkärr",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          }
        },
        "miljo": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Environment",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A seemingly wide crag offering a handful of mixed/trad routes, steep sport, as well as a fully bolted route. It sits by a meadow, out of ear- and eye-shot from the road. The approach is about 800 metres. To the left of this crag in the wooded area are some interesting boulders and shorter walls (overhangs).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          }
        },
        "access": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Access",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "There are nesting birds at the crag, therefore no climbing is recommended when the birds are nesting (the birds nest in spring, according to a local resident).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Drive along road 155 from Gothenburg towards Öckerö. Continue on Torslandavägen, which changes name to Kongahällavägen. Pass the square and the church, then turn left onto Domarringsgatan. Follow Domarringsgatan to the Västtrafik commuter parking and park there (just after the grocery store). Walk back along Domarringsvägen to Lottkärrsvägen and the large crag will be visible straight ahead. The left part of the crag has been climbed, and there's a gap in the bushes to approach where the routes begin.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder-lottkarr": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Lottkärr Routes",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Access: The bird that nests at Lottkärr Crag often does so in the same spot. Count on birds nesting at the crag every spring (at least in 2013). It's unmistakable whether there are birds or not; if so, go elsewhere.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          }
        },
        "runhallsgatan": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Runhällsgatan",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Park at the bottom of Runhällsgatan, or take the Yellow Express to the nearest stop and walk to Runhällsgatan. Climbing starts along the left side at the beginning of the road. Route lengths are 7-12m.\n\nAccess: This crag is very close to residential houses, stay low-profile and park appropriately.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumlehed"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
